 Project Overview

The **To-Do List Application** is a simple and efficient task management tool designed to help users organize, track, and manage their daily activities. This project demonstrates the implementation of core programming concepts such as data handling, user interaction, and state management in a structured and user-friendly manner.

 Objectives

* To develop a system for managing daily tasks efficiently
* To provide a simple interface for adding, updating, and deleting tasks
* To improve productivity through organized task tracking
* To demonstrate fundamental programming and UI/UX concepts

 Features

* Add new tasks
* View list of tasks
* Mark tasks as completed
* Delete tasks
* Persistent storage *(if implemented)*
* Clean and user-friendly interface

 Technologies Used



* Programming Language: Python / C / JavaScript
* Frontend: HTML, CSS 
* Backend: Node.js / Flask 
* Storage: File system / Local storage / Database

 Working Principle

The application allows users to:

1. Input tasks through a user interface
2. Store tasks in memory or storage
3. Display tasks dynamically
4. Update task status (completed/pending)
5. Remove tasks when no longer needed

The system ensures efficient task handling and improves workflow organization.

  Highlights

* Lightweight and easy to use
* Beginner-friendly implementation
* Demonstrates CRUD operations
* Can be extended into a full-stack application

